cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes an extension of an alias calculus based on program expressions, which is relevant to programming languages research. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The undecidability of determining whether two expressions may reference to the same object is a logical challenge, and the paper proposes a sound over-approximation algorithm. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): Alias analysis is an important topic in software engineering for program verification and optimization. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper introduces a notion of regular expressions to over-approximate alias expressions, which is related to formal languages and automata theory. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the main focus of the paper, alias analysis can also be relevant to security research, as it can help detect potential vulnerabilities in programs.
